9=r\cos y,40=r\sin y
y>0
\displaystyle  r^2=1681=41^2\implies r=41
\displaystyle \cos y=\frac9r=\frac9{41},\sin y=\frac{40}{41}
\displaystyle\implies 9\cos2x-40\sin2y=\frac{41}{\sqrt2}\iff\cos2x\cos y-\sin2x\sin y=\frac1{\sqrt2}
\displaystyle\implies \cos(2x+\arccos\frac9{41})=\frac1{\sqrt2}=\cos\frac\pi4
\displaystyle\implies 2x+\arccos\frac9{41}=2n\pi\pm\frac\pi4
n
a\sin(x)+b\cos(x)=\sqrt{a^2+b^2}\left(\dfrac{a}{\sqrt{a^2+b^2}} \sin{x} + \dfrac{b}{\sqrt{a^2+b^2}} \cos{x} \right)\\ =\sqrt{a^2+b^2}\left(\sin{\varphi} \sin{x} + \cos{\varphi} \cos{x} \right)=\sqrt{a^2+b^2}\cos{(x-\varphi)},
\sin{\varphi} =\dfrac{a}{\sqrt{a^2+b^2}}, \\ \cos{\varphi} =\dfrac{b}{\sqrt{a^2+b^2}}.
\tan x=\tan\alpha\implies x=n\pi+\alpha
n
